<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1399,1666]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1469,1494]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[360,566,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Cercyon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis box="[360,566,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Cercyon nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually considered as widespread in the Palearctic, Nearctic, Oriental and Afrotropical regions and introduced to Neotropical Region (
<collectingCountry box="[823,939,1503,1527]" name="Argentina" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[951,1044,1503,1527]" name="Jamaica" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, Lesser Antilles), 
<collectingCountry box="[1248,1371,1503,1527]" name="Seychelles" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Australia" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[262,411,1538,1562]" name="New Zealand" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen" box="[426,577,1538,1562]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Hansen, M. (1999) World Catalogue of Insects 2: Hydrophiloidea (s. str.) (Coleoptera). Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 416 pp." type="book" year="1999">Hansen 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen" box="[587,646,1538,1562]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Hansen, M. (2004). Family Hydrophilidae. In Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (eds.) Catalogue Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphilinoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 44 - 68." type="book" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fikacek" box="[657,813,1537,1562]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Fikacek, M. (2009) Occurrence of introduced species of the genus Cercyon (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae) in the Neotropical Region. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 68 (3 - 4), 351 - 357." type="journal article" year="2009">
Fikáček 
<number box="[752,813,1538,1562]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). At least the Asian records need to be confirmed by the study of male genitalia, because of the presence of two very similar species (
<taxonomicName authority="Wu &amp; Pu, 1995" authorityName="Wu &amp; Pu" authorityYear="1995" box="[1002,1289,1573,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Cercyon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setiger">
<emphasis box="[1002,1110,1574,1597]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">C. setiger</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wu" box="[1116,1289,1573,1597]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Jia, F. - L., Wu, W. et Pu, Z. - L. (1995) Studies on Cercyon of China (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Journal of Sun Yatsen Univiversity, Supplement, 2, 124 - 130. (in Chinese, with English abstract)." type="journal article" year="1995">
Wu &amp; Pu, 
<number box="[1233,1289,1573,1597]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ryndevich &amp; Hebauer, 2010" authorityName="Ryndevich &amp; Hebauer" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Cercyon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paranigriceps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">C. paranigriceps</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ryndevich" box="[266,599,1607,1631]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Ryndevich, S. K. &amp; Hebauer, F. (2010) Review of species of the genus Cercyon Leach, 1817 of Russia and adjacent regions. V. Subgenus Cercyon (s. str.) Leach, 1817. Cercyon nigriceps - group (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 19 (2), 330 - 340." type="journal article" year="2010">
Ryndevich &amp; Hebauer, 
<number box="[541,599,1607,1631]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) in this area (
<bibRefCitation author="Ryndevich" box="[765,1097,1607,1631]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refString="Ryndevich, S. K. &amp; Hebauer, F. (2010) Review of species of the genus Cercyon Leach, 1817 of Russia and adjacent regions. V. Subgenus Cercyon (s. str.) Leach, 1817. Cercyon nigriceps - group (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 19 (2), 330 - 340." type="journal article" year="2010">
Ryndevich &amp; Hebauer 
<number box="[1036,1097,1607,1631]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[1119,1327,1608,1632]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Cercyon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis box="[1119,1327,1608,1632]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Cercyon nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is newly recorded for Guangdong.
</paragraph>
